12.109 | Petrology | http://ocw.mit.edu/courses/earth-atmospheric-and-planetary-sciences/12-109-petrology-fall-2005 | level:Undergraduate features:Selected lecture notes prereq:12.108 instructors:T. L. Grove term:Acad Year 2016-2017: Not offered Acad Year 2017-2018: U (Fall) textbook:Hess, P. C. Origin of Igneous Rocks. Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press, 1989. textbook:Spear, F. S. Metamorphic Phase Equilibria and Pressure - Temperature - Time Paths. Chantilly, VA: Mineralogical Society of America, 1994.  description:Surveys the distribution, chemical composition, and mineral associations in rocks of the Earth's crust and upper mantle, and establishes its relation to tectonic environment. Emphasis is on the use of chemistry and physics to interpret rock forming processes. Topics include dynamics of crust and mantle melting as preserved in the chemical composition of igneous rocks and minerals, the long-term record of global climate change as preserved in the minerals of sedimentary rocks, and the time-temperature-depth record preserved in minerals of metamorphosed crustal rocks.  3-6-6 units
